  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`lastError` (which can be retrieved via command `CmdLastError` was originally designed to simplify the interface, but it creates a problem. When something fails on the server side, we would like to \"fail fast\", i.e. stop the go routine running function `Server` and release the transaction and all other resources. But if we want to allow the client to send `CmdLastError`, we would need to keep it running.\r\nTo make it simpler, please return error as an extra return value for the operations that may fail. The client will not need to perform another roundtrip and will the error straight away",
